text:
I've listed this for the playlist at my funeral or cremation. To me, it embodies the following: 

The melancholy of an end coming too soon. Yes, I may have lost the battle, but my spirit remains unbroken. Even while I must now strike the flag, life goes on. To those that stay behind: mourn now for what once was,  but focus on what lies ahead.

text: This is one of those songs that I didn't pay much attention to upon just hearing the first couple of notes. However, when just stopping and listening to the song all the way through, it's amazing. I will never forget my first reaction to hearing the song complete for the first time. Definitely one of the best Game Over/High Score themes I have ever heard. Along with Jim Power and X-Out which, coincidentally are all Amiga games...talk about an insane track record.

text: This high score theme stuck with me right from the start with its calming notes panning left and right. This is a topdown shooter so it's appropriate to have a more relaxing track while you're checking out the high scores. This game came out for the Genesis as well but I prefer the Amiga music (on the Genesis, this is the Game Over theme).
